    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i hear the \"long term\" thing all the time but for a shop with like 15 employees, these costs aren't just some \"trade-off,\" they're often what kills the business. can u dig into more detail on the specific compliance costs and how they actually compare to the supposed \"innovation\" benefits? it feels like the benefits are pretty vague compared to the actual bills they have to pay.",
