      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This is a very common and valid critique of regulatory overreach, as the burden is undeniably shifted onto smaller entities. Large corporations have the lobbying power and financial depth to navigate these complex mandates, effectively allowing them to consolidate market share. The policy, in practice, functions as a regulatory moat, favoring established giants over nimble small businesses. This dynamic is precisely why small business advocates argue that such mandates are anti-competitive rather than environmentally balanced.",
      "source": "target",
